{
  "texts": [
    "Under risk minimization framework, the objective is to learn a global minimum of R L (f), which is an optimal classifier f * (•).",
    "Similarly, the L-risk under noisy data is defined asR η L (f) = E x,ŷ [L(f (x), ŷ)],and we use f * η (•) to denote the global optimal classifier of R η L (f).",
    "We then introduce the definition for being noise tolerant.",
    "Definition 4 (Noise tolerance [11].).",
    "A loss functionL is noise tolerant, if the global minimizer of R η L (f), f * η, is also the global minimum of R L (f), f *.By the definition above, for a noise tolerant loss function L, its f * η and f * will have the same misclassification probability on clean data, which reflects that the loss function L is robust to noise."
  ]
}